# TypeScript, SCSS, tests, strict PHP (Sections B & F)

Applies to new first-party code under `web/app/plugins/` and `web/app/themes/`, and expanded admin/front-end behavior — unless the user waives (e.g. plain JS only).

## TypeScript → built JavaScript

- Author bundled/interactive code in TypeScript (not giant hand-maintained `.js` as source).
- Build with Vite, `@wordpress/scripts`, or esbuild; ship minified/prod assets.
- Document `npm run build`, `npm test`, `npm run typecheck` in README or `package.json`.
- Enqueue **built** assets, not raw `src/` TS.

## SCSS → CSS (plugins)

- Plugin styles: SCSS (e.g. `resources/scss/`) → built `.css` in `dist/` (or equivalent). Built CSS is not source of truth.
- One build command should emit both JS and CSS when both exist.

## Frontend tests

- Theme: **Vitest** + **`npm run test`** / **`npm run typecheck`** — required for new or changed TS/JS logic. **`npm run build`** runs **`typecheck`** before **Vite** so TS errors block production output. **Lint + format:** **`npm run lint`** (ESLint + Prettier check) — **`13-mandatory-lint.mdc`**, skills **`linting-php-eslint`**, **`prettier-tailwind`**. Full testing policy: **`10-testing-mandatory.mdc`**, skill **`testing-php-vitest`**.
- Plugins may use Vitest, Jest, `node:test`, Playwright — same bar: tests pass before done.

## PHP

- Every new PHP file: `declare(strict_types=1);` after `<?php` and file docblock.
- Non-trivial PHP: PHPUnit; **`composer test`** must pass. Sage: **`tests/`**, **`phpunit.xml.dist`**, integration via **`composer run test:integration`** when WP is required.
- Full policy: **`10-testing-mandatory.mdc`**.

Plugin scaffold, templates, and git: `04-wordpress-plugins.mdc` + skill `wordpress-plugins`.
